Create Funnels¶

In [39]:
# Funnels
# Information is provided to you
savings_screens = ["Saving1",
                    "Saving2",
                    "Saving2Amount",
                    "Saving4",
                    "Saving5",
                    "Saving6",
                    "Saving7",
                    "Saving8",
                    "Saving9",
                    "Saving10"]
df["SavingCount"] = df[savings_screens].sum(axis=1)
df = df.drop(columns=savings_screens)

# Credit monitoring screens
cm_screens = ["Credit1",
               "Credit2",
               "Credit3",
               "Credit3Container",
               "Credit3Dashboard"]
df["CMCount"] = df[cm_screens].sum(axis=1)
df = df.drop(columns=cm_screens)

# Credit card screens
cc_screens = ["CC1",
                "CC1Category",
                "CC3"]
df["CCCount"] = df[cc_screens].sum(axis=1)
df = df.drop(columns=cc_screens)

 # Loan screens
loan_screens = ["Loan",
               "Loan2",
               "Loan3",
               "Loan4"]
df["LoansCount"] = df[loan_screens].sum(axis=1)
df = df.drop(columns=loan_screens)

X_test = X_test2

First Model Building¶

In [54]:
# import the appropriate model 
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
In [55]:
# Fitting the model to the training set
# screens can be correlated to each other and we created the funnel features 
# other correlations may exist between screens. l1 regularization penalizes any particular field 
# that is strongly correlated to the response variable
classifier = LogisticRegression(random_state = 0, penalty ='l2')
classifier.fit(X_train, y_train)
Out[55]:
LogisticRegression(random_state=0)
In [56]:
# Predicting the test set
y_pred = classifier.predict(X_test)
In [57]:
# Evaluating the results
# Confusion Matrix
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, f1_score, recall_score, precision_score
cm =confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
In [58]:
print('accuracy score is:',accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))

print('precision score is:',precision_score(y_test, y_pred))  # tp / (tp + fp)
